It can be said that basketball / soccer fields are very popular. Several picnic tables and benches are scattered and widely used, as evidenced by the many trash cans that still abound with vestiges of picnics and other activities. But I should have said that they are underused these garbage cans, because despite their strategic locations, there is unfortunately a lot of waste that does not go. Can someone explain to me why a person who is able to bring a full bottle of the beverage of his choice to the park does not have the ability to drop it into the trash can three feet away from her once empty? Yet I was under the impression that when she is full she weighs the most !! 
Thanks, a bit of civility to keep our beautiful green space pleasant and free of unpleasant creatures (because your abandoned waste anywhere attracts rats and other vermin with which nobody wants to live together in this beautiful park)
